items.abstract: <jats:p>The cathodoluminescence properties of rare-earth (RE = Ce, Eu, Tb) doped nanocrystalline phosphors (<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="E1"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>Y</mml:mtext><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mtext>O</mml:mtext><mml:mn>3</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:math>,<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="E2"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>Y</mml:mtext><mml:mn>3</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mtext>A</mml:mtext><mml:msub><mml:mtext>l</mml:mtext><mml:mn>5</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mtext>O</mml:mtext><mml:mrow><mml:mn>12</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math>) were investigated. Their structure and morphology were determined and correlated with optical properties. The effect of grain sizes on emission yield of RE doped nanophosphors has been investigated. A possibility of application of RE doped nanophosphors for efficient field emission display (FED) devices has been discussed.</jats:p>
